1 A BILL for an Act to amend and reenact subsection 3 of section 54-44-04.6 of the North Dakota
2 Century Code, relating to state surplus motor vehicles.
3 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
4 SECTION 1. AMENDMENT. Subsection 3 of section 54-44-04.6 of the North Dakota
5 Century Code is amended and reenacted as follows:
6 3. Surplus property must be transferred at fair market value to state agencies, political
7 subdivisions, and nonprofit organizations eligible to receive federal surplus property
8 under the Federal Property Administrative Services Act of 1949, as amended. Eligible
9 organizations must be notified of the availability of property on a regular basis. Surplus
10 motor vehicles must be made available first, for fourteen days, to political subdivisions
11 for purchase at a cost of thirty percent less than fair market value.
